{"type":"user","uuid":"c343dc4b-b465-49d6-ac94-147beeffa22b","session_id":"7d08652e-4d6f-459a-a10d-c983fbe8d044","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde2985465d8cea7a8ebbd95f4776","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me compile the comprehensive code review report:\n\n---\n\n## 📋 F-001 Phase 6: Code Review Report\n\n### Review Summary\n\n| Dimension | Status | Notes |\n|-----------|--------|-------|\n| Spec Compliance | ✅ PASS | All 12 Acceptance Criteria verified |\n| Plan Adherence | ✅ PASS | All interfaces match plan.md |\n| Code Quality | ✅ PASS | Clean, modular, well-tested |\n| Security | ✅ PASS | Path traversal protection in place |\n| Consistency | ✅ PASS | Python/JS parity verified |\n| Test Coverage | ✅ PASS | 29 tests, all user stories covered |\n\n---\n\n### 1. Spec Compliance Analysis\n\n| AC | Requirement | Status | Evidence |\n|----|-------------|--------|----------|\n| AC-1.1 | `loadPipelineInfraConfig()` returns frozen config | ✅ | `config-loader.js:174` - `Object.freeze({...})` |\n| AC-1.2 | Structured error with code, hint, field in context | ✅ | `config-loader.js:66-82` - `throwInfraError()` |\n| AC-1.3 | ENV + CLI override, CLI priority | ✅ | `config-loader.js:99-101` - argMap checked before env |\n| AC-2.1 | Feature specs in `.prizmkit/specs/{slug}/` | ✅ | `path-policy.js:35` |\n| AC-2.2 | Feature state in `dev-pipeline/state/features/{F-NNN}/` | ✅ | `path-policy.js:36` |\n| AC-2.3 | Session logs in `sessions/{sessionId}/logs/` | ✅ | `path-policy.js:42` |\n| AC-2.4 | Daemon logs in correct locations | ✅ | `path-policy.js:63-70` |\n| AC-3.1 | `buildPipelineCommand()` constructs correct paths | ✅ | `script-runner.js:35-133` |\n| AC-3.2 | `executePipelineCommand()` returns standardized result | ✅ | `script-runner.js:212-282` |\n| AC-3.3 | run/status/stop/logs/retry/reset operations | ✅ | All 6 actions implemented |\n| AC-4.1 | `npm run typecheck` passes | ✅ | Verified - 0 errors |\n| AC-4.2 | `npm run lint` passes | ✅ | Verified - 0 warnings |\n| AC-4.3 | tsconfig.json includes target files | ✅ | `tsconfig.json:15-17` |\n\n---\n\n### 2. Plan Adherence Analysis\n\n| Planned Interface | Implementation | Status |\n|-------------------|----------------|--------|\n| `loadPipelineInfraConfig(input)` | `config-loader.js:95` | ✅ Matches |\n| `computeFeatureSlug(featureId, title)` | `path-policy.js:14` | ✅ Matches |\n| `resolveFeaturePaths(input)` | `path-policy.js:29` | ✅ Matches |\n| `resolveBugPaths(input)` | `path-policy.js:47` | ✅ Matches |\n| `resolveDaemonLogPaths(projectRoot)` | `path-policy.js:63` | ✅ Matches |\n| `buildPipelineCommand(req, config)` | `script-runner.js:35` | ✅ Matches |\n| `executePipelineCommand(req)` | `script-runner.js:212` | ✅ Matches |\n| `createPipelineControlService(options)` | `pipeline-control-service.js:14` | ✅ Matches |\n\n---\n\n### 3. Code Quality Analysis\n\n**Strengths:**\n- Clean separation of concerns (4 infra modules + 1 service layer)\n- Immutability via `Object.freeze()` for config objects\n- Pure functions where appropriate (e.g., `computeFeatureSlug`)\n- Consistent error handling pattern with structured error objects\n- Well-documented Python module with docstrings\n\n**Minor Observations:**\n- No JSDoc comments in JS modules (acceptable for internal infra)\n- `throwInfraError` in config-loader.js creates a new Error and attaches infraError properties - slightly unusual pattern but functional\n\n---\n\n### 4. Security Analysis\n\n| Check | Status | Evidence |\n|-------|--------|----------|\n| Path traversal protection | ✅ | `SAFE_SEGMENT_PATTERN` + `..` rejection in `path-policy.js:1-12` |\n| No hardcoded secrets | ✅ | All secrets from env/config |\n| Input validation | ✅ | `ensureValidRequest()`, `ensureTargetId()`, `assertSafeSegment()` |\n| Script execution safety | ✅ | Script paths validated, no shell injection |\n| Config immutability | ✅ | `Object.freeze()` prevents mutation |\n\n---\n\n### 5. Consistency Analysis\n\n| Aspect | Status | Notes |\n|--------|--------|-------|\n| Python/JS path parity | ✅ | Verified by `path-policy-python-compat.test.js` |\n| Error code consistency | ✅ | All modules use `INFRA_ERROR_CODES` |\n| Naming conventions | ✅ | Consistent camelCase for JS, snake_case for Python |\n| Module structure | ✅ | Matches plan.md architecture diagram |\n\n---\n\n### 6. Test Coverage Analysis\n\n| Test File | Tests | Coverage Target |\n|-----------|-------|-----------------|\n| `config-loader.test.js` | 4 | US-1 validation |\n| `path-policy.test.js` | 5 | US-2 paths + security |\n| `path-policy-python-compat.test.js` | 3 | Python/JS parity |\n| `error-codes.test.js` | 4 | Error object contracts |\n| `script-runner.test.js` | 3 | US-3 command building |\n| `pipeline-control-service.test.js` | 2 | Service API contract |\n| `config.test.js` (existing) | 2 | Integration with config.js |\n| `f001-user-stories.integration.test.js` | 4 | All 4 user stories E2E |\n| **Total** | **29** | **100% user stories** |\n\n---\n\n### 7. Integration Test Verification\n\n**User Story Coverage in `f001-user-stories.integration.test.js`:**\n\n| User Story | Test Case | Status |\n|------------|-----------|--------|\n| US-1 | Config loading + validation errors | ✅ Lines 77-109 |\n| US-2 | Path policy + Python compatibility | ✅ Lines 111-160 |\n| US-3 | Pipeline control service + edge cases | ✅ Lines 162-302 |\n| US-4 | Static checks + startup flow | ✅ Lines 304-366 |\n\n**Edge Cases Tested:**\n- ✅ Timeout handling (`EXEC_TIMEOUT`)\n- ✅ Non-zero exit codes (`EXEC_FAILED`)\n- ✅ Missing scripts (`SCRIPT_NOT_FOUND`)\n- ✅ Missing targetId validation\n- ✅ Path traversal rejection\n\n---\n\n### 8. Findings\n\n| # | Severity | File | Line | Description |\n|---|----------|------|------|-------------|\n| 1 | LOW | `script-runner.js` | 205-210 | `scriptExists()` has special case for 'python3'/'node' but these commands are never used directly in the current implementation. Minor dead code. |\n| 2 | LOW | `config-loader